## nginx

### Upstream keepalive (required)

```nginx
upstream backend {
    server backend:8000;
    keepalive 32;
}
```

All proxy locations that forward to `backend` must use HTTP/1.1 and clear the `Connection` header:

```nginx
proxy_http_version 1.1;
proxy_set_header Connection "";
```

WebSocket locations are exempt (they set `Connection "upgrade"` explicitly).

### Timeouts (required on general API proxy)

```nginx
proxy_connect_timeout 5s;   # fail fast if backend is down
proxy_send_timeout 30s;     # time to send request body
proxy_read_timeout 120s;    # time to receive response (long AI calls)
```

WebSocket locations use `proxy_read_timeout 3600s` / `proxy_send_timeout 3600s` — long-lived connections.

### Rate limiting zones

| Zone | Rate | Applies to |
|---|---|---|
| `api` | 60r/m | All `/api/` |
| `auth` | 10r/m | `/api/auth/` |
| `chat` | 20r/m | `/api/ws/chat` |

Rate limiting lives entirely in nginx. The Python app has no rate-limit logic.

### Security headers (required on HTTPS server block)

```nginx
Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=63072000; includeSubDomains; preload
X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
X-Frame-Options: DENY
Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
Permissions-Policy: camera=(self), microphone=(), geolocation=()
```

`Content-Security-Policy` belongs on the frontend, not the nginx server block.

### Metrics endpoint restriction (required)

`/metrics` must be restricted to loopback and RFC1918 ranges only. Never expose Prometheus metrics publicly.

