## CORS

### Origin locking (enforced at startup)

`_enforce_cors()` in `config.py` raises `RuntimeError` at import time if `CORS_ORIGINS` is `"*"` or empty in staging or production. This is not a warning — it is a hard crash.

Set `CORS_ORIGINS` to the exact frontend domain(s):
```
CORS_ORIGINS=https://app.yourdomain.com
```

For Vercel preview URLs use `CORS_ORIGIN_REGEX`:
```
CORS_ORIGIN_REGEX=https://frontend-.*\.vercel\.app
```

### Allowed methods and headers (explicitly enumerated)

```python
allow_methods=["GET", "POST", "PUT", "PATCH", "DELETE", "OPTIONS"]
allow_headers=["Authorization", "Content-Type", "X-Request-ID"]
```

Do not use `["*"]` for methods or headers. `allow_credentials=True` is required (JWTs sent as Bearer tokens).

