## Connection pool

All pool settings are configurable via env vars and documented in `config.py`. Defaults are conservative and safe for a single-worker deployment.

| Var | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `PG_POOL_MIN` | 2 | Minimum idle connections |
| `PG_POOL_MAX` | 10 | Maximum pool size |
| `PG_ACQUIRE_TIMEOUT` | 10s | Max wait for a free connection |
| `PG_COMMAND_TIMEOUT` | 30s | Max time for a single SQL statement |

For multi-worker deployments (`WORKERS > 1`), `PG_POOL_MAX` per worker multiplies. Set it accordingly (e.g., 2 workers × 5 max = 10 total connections).

`PG_ACQUIRE_TIMEOUT` is the primary defense against connection starvation cascades — when the pool is exhausted, requests fail fast with a clear error rather than queueing indefinitely.

